olive oil
1 avocado
2 radish
2 sprig spring onion
1 orange
1 packet Halloumi
1 packet Slivered Almonds
1 tsp honey
1 packet balsamic glaze
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
1 packet mint

• Slice avocado in half, scoop out flesh and thinly slice.
• Thinly slice radish and spring onion.
• Peel and thinly slice orange into wedges.
• Cut halloumi into 1cm slices.
• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Toast slivered almonds, tossing, until golden, 2-3 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.

• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook halloumi, until golden brown, 1-2 minutes each side.
• Remove pan from heat, then add the honey and turn to coat.

• In a medium bowl, combine balsamic glaze, a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt and pepper.
• To the bowl, add orange, radish, spring onion and mixed salad leaves. Toss to combine.

• Divide orange and radish salad between bowls.
• Top with avocado and glazed halloumi. Sprinkle over toasted almonds and tear over mint to serve. Enjoy!